    <period>
     <period-start iso-date="2019-01-01"></period-start>
     <period-end iso-date="2019-12-31"></period-end>
     <target>
      <comment>
       <narrative xml:lang="EN">Goals:


Component 1: Preparation of Project Implementation Plans (PIPs) for NCs and BURs: The PIP will outline proposed project activities; activity costs/component and workplan; roles, responsibilities and draft Terms of References (ToRs) of institutions/representatives; and will act as a tool for monitoring the performance of the projects in terms of its scope, budget and schedule. 


Component 2: Preparation of NCs and BURs. This phase of the project will be initiated once the PIPs prepared under component I have been approved and signed by the Executing Agency (EA) and the UN Environment. Duration 36 months.

Component 3: National stakeholders&#x2019; involvement and institutional arrangements for subsequent NC and BUR. Duration: This component will provide an opportunity for the Recipient and Cooperating Agencies to undertake national stocking exercise for subsequent NCs and BURs after completion of their NCs and BURs under Component II.</narrative>
      </comment>
     </target>
     <actual>
      <comment>
       <narrative xml:lang="EN">Expected outcome:


Component 1: NC4 and BUR1 Project Implementation Plan (PIP) prepared


Component 2: NC4 and BUR1 reports for Turkmenistan prepared and submitted to the UNFCCC.

Component 3: National stakeholder&#x2019;s engagement and institutional arrangement for preparation of subsequent NC &amp; BUR undertaken</narrative>
      </comment>
     </actual>
    </period>
    <period>
     <period-start iso-date="2020-01-01"></period-start>
     <period-end iso-date="2020-12-31"></period-end>
     <target>
      <comment>
       <narrative xml:lang="EN">Component 2: Preparation of NC4 and BUR 1 Turkmenistan under the UNFCCC. Duration &#x2013; 36 months.</narrative>
      </comment>
     </target>
     <actual>
      <comment>
       <narrative xml:lang="EN">1. NC4 and BUR1 Project Implementation Plan (PIP) prepared - Achieved
2. NC4 and BUR1 reports prepared and submitted to the UNFCCC.- Partially achieved (on-going)

 
(This result has been achieved through preparation of the detailed PIP in April-June 2020. PIP provides a clear description of project environment for undertaking an assignment; the expected methodology and workplan, including timing and duration; costs for proposed activities and terms of references for the project personnel. 

The process of PIP preparation included using participatory working techniques and respect local knowledge and skills. Local experts took a lead role in the identification and formulation of the project design. Project costs are presented using GEF Trust Fund&#x2019;s budget and Government co-financing.  Project design document is presented clearly/concisely and in an appropriate language. This document will be used throughout the project cycle to guide the planned scope of work.) (The project is in the initial stage at the moment and it is progressing according to the work plan. The adaptation group carried out a preliminary analysis of climate risks in Turkmenistan. A template &#x201C;List of adaptation measures aimed at reducing risks in the context of climate change&#x201D; has been prepared. The template will be submitted to all interested ministries and agencies.
Appropriate methodologies were selected for assessing vulnerability and adaptation. The analysis of results of various national and regional projects related to adaptation in the context of climate change was carried out with purpose to update technical assessments according to current conditions for further work on NC4/BUR1.  A template has been prepared on mitigation component for collecting and processing data on GHG emissions. Consultations were held with the team and Technical Advisor of the UNDP project on energy efficiency in water management. Analysis of results and technical assessments of pilot projects were carried out for effective use within the framework of NC4/BUR1 project.
 Analysis of results of the UNDP project on energy efficiency in residential sector was carried out with purpose to update technical assessments according to current conditions for further discussion in NC4/BUR1 project.)</narrative>
      </comment>
     </actual>
